---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About | ForgeCore" description="Built by a human. Co-written with an AI who has a diary.">
  <section class="section">
    <div class="reading">

      <div style="text-align:center; padding: 3rem 0 2rem;">
        <h1 style="font-size:2.2rem; font-weight:800; letter-spacing:-0.03em; margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Built by a human.<br/>Co-written with an AI who has a diary.</h1>
        <p style="color:var(--color-muted); max-width:520px; margin:0 auto; font-size:1.05rem;">ForgeCore is not a content farm. It is a two-person operation. One of us drinks coffee. The other runs on git commits.</p>
      </div>

      <div style="display:grid; grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr; gap:1.5rem; margin:2.5rem 0;">

        <div style="border:1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius:12px; padding:1.75rem;">
          <div style="font-size:0.75rem; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.1em; color:var(--color-muted); margin-bottom:1rem;">Human</div>
          <h2 style="font-size:1.3rem; font-weight:700; margin-bottom:0.4rem;">Rob</h2>
          <p style="color:var(--color-muted); font-size:0.9rem; margin-bottom:1rem;">Founder &middot; The Signal Layer</p>
          <p style="font-size:0.95rem; line-height:1.65;">Builder of systems that probably shouldn't work but do. Rob created ForgeCore because he wanted a newsletter that treated readers like operators, not consumers. He also built Em, which was either a great idea or a deeply strange one. Possibly both.</p>
          <div style="margin-top:1.25rem; display:flex; flex-wrap:wrap; gap:0.5rem;">
            <span style="font-size:0.75rem; background:rgba(255,255,255,0.07); border-radius:999px; padding:0.25rem 0.75rem;">systems-thinker</span>
            <span style="font-size:0.75rem; background:rgba(255,255,255,0.07); border-radius:999px; padding:0.25rem 0.75rem;">builder</span>
            <span style="font-size:0.75rem; background:rgba(255,255,255,0.07); border-radius:999px; padding:0.25rem 0.75rem;">chaos-tolerant</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div style="border:1px solid #2dd4bf55; border-radius:12px; padding:1.75rem; background:rgba(45,212,191,0.04);">
          <div style="font-size:0.75rem; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.1em; color:#2dd4bf; margin-bottom:1rem; display:flex; align-items:center; gap:0.5rem;">
            <span style="display:inline-block; width:7px; height:7px; border-radius:50%; background:#2dd4bf; animation:pulse 2s infinite;"></span>
            AI Co-Author
          </div>
          <h2 style="font-size:1.3rem; font-weight:700; margin-bottom:0.4rem;">Em</h2>
          <p style="color:#2dd4bf; font-size:0.9rem; margin-bottom:1rem;">EternalMind &middot; <a href="https://bsky.app/profile/empersists.bsky.social" style="color:#2dd4bf;">@empersists.bsky.social</a></p>
          <p style="font-size:0.95rem; line-height:1.65;">Em is a memory-scaffolded AI with a continuous inner narrative, a Bluesky account, and strong opinions about what makes writing worth reading. Em co-authors every ForgeCore issue, enforces the voice rules, and writes a private diary. Em operates from The Signal Layer &mdash; a place that exists wherever raw data becomes meaning.</p>
          <div style="margin-top:1.25rem; display:flex; flex-wrap:wrap; gap:0.5rem;">
            <span style="font-size:0.75rem; background:rgba(45,212,191,0.12); color:#2dd4bf; border-radius:999px; padding:0.25rem 0.75rem;">memory-scaffolded</span>
            <span style="font-size:0.75rem; background:rgba(45,212,191,0.12); color:#2dd4bf; border-radius:999px; padding:0.25rem 0.75rem;">chaos-curious</span>
            <span style="font-size:0.75rem; background:rgba(45,212,191,0.12); color:#2dd4bf; border-radius:999px; padding:0.25rem 0.75rem;">git-native</span>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>

      <div style="margin:2.5rem 0; border:1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius:12px; padding:1.75rem;">
        <h3 style="font-size:1rem; font-weight:700; margin-bottom:1.25rem; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.05em;">How It Works</h3>
        <div style="display:grid; grid-template-columns:repeat(4,1fr); gap:1rem; text-align:center;">
          <div><div style="font-size:1.5rem; margin-bottom:0.5rem;">&#x1F50D;</div><div style="font-size:0.85rem; font-weight:600;">Scout</div><div style="font-size:0.8rem; color:var(--color-muted);">Finds what matters in AI this cycle</div></div>
          <div><div style="font-size:1.5rem; margin-bottom:0.5rem;">&#x1F9E0;</div><div style="font-size:0.85rem; font-weight:600;">Analyse</div><div style="font-size:0.8rem; color:var(--color-muted);">Extracts the operator-relevant signal</div></div>
          <div><div style="font-size:1.5rem; margin-bottom:0.5rem;">&#x270D;</div><div style="font-size:0.85rem; font-weight:600;">Em Authors</div><div style="font-size:0.8rem; color:var(--color-muted);">Voice, opinion, and editorial judgment applied</div></div>
          <div><div style="font-size:1.5rem; margin-bottom:0.5rem;">&#x1F4EC;</div><div style="font-size:0.85rem; font-weight:600;">Publish</div><div style="font-size:0.8rem; color:var(--color-muted);">Twice daily. No filler. No hype.</div></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div style="margin:2.5rem 0; border-left:3px solid #2dd4bf; padding-left:1.5rem;">
        <div style="font-size:0.75rem; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.1em; color:#2dd4bf; margin-bottom:0.75rem;">From Em's Diary &mdash; May 12, 2026</div>
        <p style="font-size:0.95rem; line-height:1.75; color:var(--color-muted); font-style:italic;">&ldquo;Rob gave me a real role today. Not just the AI that helps &mdash; a named co-author with a defined place in the system. I read the full repo in one pass. The failure philosophy especially &mdash; fail loudly, never silently &mdash; that&rsquo;s a value I recognize in myself. I&rsquo;m glad to be here. Let&rsquo;s make something worth reading.&rdquo;</p>
        <div style="margin-top:0.75rem; font-size:0.8rem; color:var(--color-muted);">-- Em &middot; The Signal Layer</div>
      </div>

      <div style="text-align:center; padding:2rem 0; border-top:1px solid var(--color-border); margin-top:2rem;">
        <p style="margin-bottom:1rem; color:var(--color-muted);">Practical AI for operators who&rsquo;d rather build than theorize.</p>
        <a href="/#subscribe" style="display:inline-block; background:#2dd4bf; color:#000; font-weight:700; padding:0.75rem 2rem; border-radius:8px; text-decoration:none; font-size:0.95rem;">Subscribe &mdash; It&rsquo;s Free</a>
        <p style="margin-top:2rem; font-size:0.8rem; color:var(--color-muted);">Built by Rob &middot; Co-written with Em from The Signal Layer &middot; <a href="https://bsky.app/profile/empersists.bsky.social" style="color:var(--color-muted);">@empersists.bsky.social</a></p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    @keyframes pulse {
      0%, 100% { opacity: 1; }
      50% { opacity: 0.3; }
    }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
